00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:04.270
Now let delta t go to 0.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:06.010
So what does this
equation become?

00:10:11.750 --> 00:10:16.510
Then everybody knows that as
the limit of delta t goes to 0,

00:10:16.510 --> 00:10:20.560
I replace deltas by--

00:10:20.560 --> 00:10:25.270
so this delta A divided by
delta t that has a meaning.

00:10:25.270 --> 00:10:28.940
The top has a meaning and
the bottom has for me.

00:10:28.940 --> 00:10:33.580
But then the limit, it's the
ratio that has a meaning.

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:37.255
So dA by itself, I don't
attach a meaning to that.

00:10:37.255 --> 00:10:38.790
That's infinitesimal.

00:10:38.790 --> 00:10:42.720
It's the limit, so that's why
I wanted a delta over a delta

00:10:42.720 --> 00:10:44.160
so I could do calculus.

00:10:44.160 --> 00:10:47.070
So what happens now
is delta t goes to 0.

00:10:47.070 --> 00:10:49.500
And, of course, as
delta t goes to 0,

00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:51.720
that carries delta A to 0.

00:10:51.720 --> 00:10:53.160
So that becomes A inverse.

00:10:55.980 --> 00:11:01.390
And what does this approach
as delta t goes to 0?

00:11:01.390 --> 00:11:03.710
dA dt with that minus sign.

00:11:03.710 --> 00:11:06.650
Oh, I've got to
remember the minus sign.

00:11:06.650 --> 00:11:09.890
The minus sign is in here.

00:11:09.890 --> 00:11:12.060
So I'm bringing
out the minus sign.

00:11:12.060 --> 00:11:15.380
Then this was A
inverse, as we had.

00:11:15.380 --> 00:11:16.930
And that's dA dt.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:22.310
And that's A inverse.

00:11:22.310 --> 00:11:26.660
That's our formula,
a nice formula,

00:11:26.660 --> 00:11:32.150
which sort of belongs
in people's knowledge.

00:11:32.150 --> 00:11:38.250
You recognize that if
A was a 1 by 1 matrix,

00:11:38.250 --> 00:11:45.060
we could call it x, instead of
A. If A was a 1 by 1 matrix x,

00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:49.830
then I'm saying the formula
for the derivative of 1

00:11:49.830 --> 00:11:51.570
over x, right?

00:11:51.570 --> 00:11:56.010
A inverse just 1 by 1
case is just 1 over x.

00:11:56.010 --> 00:12:00.120
So the derivative of 1-- or
maybe t, I should be saying.

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:05.580
If A is just t, then the
derivative of 1 over t with

00:12:05.580 --> 00:12:09.790
respect to t is....?

00:12:09.790 --> 00:12:11.680
Is minus 1 over t squared.

00:12:15.580 --> 00:12:18.010
The 1 by 1 case we know.

00:12:18.010 --> 00:12:19.330
That's what calculus does.

00:12:19.330 --> 00:12:23.640
And now we're able to
